Title : Management of congenital bilateral temporomandibular joint ankylosis with secondary mandibular hypoplasia.
Date : 2008
Publication_type : Journal Article
Abstract : The aim of this article is to present the course of the condition in a case of congenital temporomandibular joint ankylosis that caused facial disfigurement, significant reduction of mouth opening, difficulty in feeding and breathing, and general interference with physical development.
